:hairstyle
1,Afro (a kinky, bushy style of the 1960s and eaerly 1970s)
2,Afro puffs (kinky, bushy puffs worn on either side of the head)
3,American Indian (long and straight; parted in the middle, braided or worn in a ponytail)
4,bangs (a fringe of hair falling over the forehead)
5,Beatle cut (the classic bowl-like cut that reached the height of popularity in the 1960s; also known as the Moe (Three Stooges) cut)
6,beaver tail (a flat loop of hair worn over the nape of the neck, originating in 1865; also known as a banging chignon)
7,beehive (a very tall, dome-like style reminiscent of a beehive; popularly worn from the late 1950s to early 1960s)
8,bob (a woman's or child's short haircut with or without bangs)
9,bouffant (a full, puffed-out style dependent on copious amounts of hairspray to keep it together)
10,boyish bob (a woman's very short haircut shingled in the back)
11,braids (plaited hair; may be worn down the back, to the sides, or wound around the head)
12,brushed back severely (brushed abruptly away from the face)
13,bun (a tight roll held fast near the top of the head or near the nape of the neck; also known as a French roll)
14,chignon (a knot or roll twisted into a circle or figure either at the back of the head)
15,China doll (short and straight with bangs)
16,Cleopatra (long and straight down the sides)
17,coiled (a coil of plaits, worn on back, to the side, or on top of the head)
18,corkscrew curls (long, dangling curls resembling corkscrews)
19,cornrows (a style in which hair is braided into tight rows close to the head)
20,crew cut (a flattop or buzz cut, usually only worn by men)
21,dreadlocks (tight, dangling, shoulder-length braids originally worn by the Rastafarians of Jamaica)
22,ducktail (a classic 1950s style in which the hair was oiled, combed back over the ears, and molded up in back to form what looked like the tai lof a duck; also known as a DA (duck's ass))
23,earmuffs (braids worn in circles over the ears)
24,elflocks (tangled or matted hair)
25,empire cone (a style, revived by Madonna, in which the hair is pulled through a cone-like contrivance and worn as a ponytail from the top of the head)
26,fade (also known as the gumby or the slope, a flattop cut at a slant, sometimes with shaved lines or designs through it, a popular style among men in the 1990s)
27,feather cut (a women's layered, slightly curled bob, popular in the 1960s and early 1970s)
28,fishbone braid (a braid, reminiscent of the spine of a fish, worn down the back; also known as a French braid)
29,flattop (crew cut, buzz cut)
30,flip (a woman's cut in which the hair ends in curls on the sides, usually worn with bangs)
31,French braid (a braid, reminiscent of the spine of a fish, worn down the back)
32,hardened with hairspray (overly sprayed, giving a brittle or lacquered look)
33,Mandinko (a look popularized by the television hero, Mr. T., comprised of a Mohawk haircut worn with a beard, mustache, and sideburns)
34,marcel wave (tight waves arranged around the head with a curling iron, originating in the 1890s)
35,Mohawk (a shaved head with a brush of hair one to six inches high running down the middle of the scalp; originally worn by Mohawk Indians but revived by punk rockers in the 1980s)
36,pageboy (a style featuring bangs and hair falling straight to the sides with ends turned under)
37,pigtails (braids hanging on either side of the head)
38,pixie (a short cut characterized by points around the forehead and face)
39,pompadour (a style in which hair is swept up high from the forehead, popular in the early 1900s as the "Gibson Girl" look and revived in slightly different modes since)
40,poodle cut (a short, curly haircut, similar to a poodle's coat)
41,porcupine (a punk haircut characterized by long spikes or strands of hair standing on end down the middle of the head)
42,pulled back (a style in which the hair is pulled back and tied with a ribbon or held with barrette)
43,punk (any Mohawk, porcupine, dyed, shaved, sculpted or spiked hair)
44,receding hairline (progressive balding, from front to back)
45,roach (hair brushed back to form a roll)
46,rooster mane (male cut characterized by hair gathered at the top from front to back, or a Mohawk style)
47,scupltured (hair styled with shaved-in designs, logos, or initials; also moused hair arranged in various fashions)
48,shag (a shaggy bob worn with bangs)
49,shock (bushy mass)
50,skinhead (a shaved head)
51,spikes (a punk style characterized by long spikes of moussed or gelled hair, sometimes dyed)
52,spit curl (a curl of hair kept together and attached to the face with saliva)
53,tail (style of the late)
54,tonsure (a fringed circle of hair surrounding a bald crown)
55,topknot (a knot tied at the crown of the head)
56,Veronica Lake (popular in the 1940s and again in the 1960s, a style characterized by the hair parted to one side to partially cover one eye; named after the actress who originated the look)
57,wedge (the wildly popular Dorothy Hamill look of the 1970s; the hair on the front and sides is the same length, with the back tapered close to the head)
58,widow's peak (hair tapering to a point on the forehead)

