:!blemish
1,Age spots (brown spots on the face and hands, occurring in the elderly; also known as liver spots)
2,Chloasma (also known as the "mask of pregnancy," brown patched that frequently appear on the skin of pregnant women; it sometimes forms a simple, false mustache over the upper lip)
3,Dermatitis (any inflamed skin)
4,Eczema (skin inflammation characterized by redness, crusting, and the formation of pimple and vesicles)
5,Lentigo (a brownish spot unrelated to a freckle)
6,Liver spots (yellowish-brown, red or black spots or patches on the skin, often appearing in the elderly and formerly attributed to liver disfunction; also known as age spots)
7,Lupus erythematosus (a skin disease characterized by a scaly rash, often a butterfly pattern over the nose and cheeks)
8,Nevus (any birthmark)
9,Piebald skin (a mysterious skin condition characterized by patches of skin lacking pigment; also known as vitiligo)
10,Port wine stain (a wine-colored birthmark, as on the forehead of former Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev)
11,Rosacea (an inflammatory skin disorder characterized by small pimples and the dilation of facial capillaries, giving a raw, red appearance; often found onthe nose and sometimes on other parts of the face; the disorder is common among people originating from the British Isles, alcoholics, and people who blush easily)
12,Strawberry birthmark (a common birthmark, reminiscent of a strawberry)
13,Zits (slang for pimples, acne)
14,Bloodshot eyes (red and irrated)
15,Cataracts (a clouding of the lens)
16,Glass eye (a false eye of any color)
17,Helerochroma iridis (the condition of having one brown eye and one blue eye; it occurs in approximately 1 in every 1,000 people)
18,Nystagmus (a disorder in which one or both eyes jerk or move involuntarily, caused by brain lesions, inflammation, alcohol or drug abuse; sometimes present congenitally)
19,Variegated eyes (flecked with various colors)
20,Walleyed (having a whitish or grayish eye or eyes)
21,Yellowed scleras (yellowed whites of the eyes, sometimes seen in older people)

